Mircea Lucescu is a highly decorated Romanian football manager and former player. As a player, he won 6 Romanian league titles with Dinamo Bucure»ôti and made 70 appearances for the Romania national team. As a manager, he has had great success in Romania, Italy, Turkey, Ukraine, and Russia, winning numerous league and cup titles. He is best known for his 12-year spell in charge of Shakhtar Donetsk, where he became the club's most successful coach ever.
